/home/archon/slopetale/blueprint/src/chapters/local-structure.tex:  The map $A \to A^S$ is ind-Zariski by \Cref{lemma:ind-Zariski-products} and $A^S \to A^f_{q}$ is also ind-Zariski by \Cref{thm:colim-open-closed-localizations-surj-ind-zariski}.  The composition $A \to A^f_{q}$ is therefore ind-Zariski as well by \Cref{thm:ind-Zariski-composition}. By \Cref{thm:ind-Zariski-identifies-local-rings}, $A \to A^f_{q}$ identifies local rings. The last sentence is a direct consequence of \Cref{thm:colim-open-closed-localizations-surj-ind-zariski}.
